{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17636998","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17636998"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T18:36:31+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T18:36:31+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17619"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17619","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17619"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10333"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71656"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10333","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10333"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17619"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57152"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"4948"},{"type":"tags","id":"7752"},{"type":"tags","id":"7826"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24176"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24179"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71656","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/71656"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA researcher conducts a study comparing two different treatments for pneumonia. After analysing the data, they obtain a p-value of 0.03.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the interpretation of this p-value?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["The treatments are 97% likely to be different","There is a 3% probability of obtaining these results if the null hypothesis is true","The difference between treatments is clinically significant","The study findings are 97% accurate","There is a 3% chance the research hypothesis is true"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct interpretation is that there is a \u003Cstrong\u003E3% probability of obtaining these results if the null hypothesis is true\u003C/strong\u003E. The p-value represents the probability of observing results as extreme or more extreme than those obtained, assuming no real difference exists between treatments. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhile this result would be considered statistically significant at the conventional p \u0026lt; 0.05 threshold, the p-value alone cannot tell us about the magnitude or clinical relevance of any observed difference between treatments. It also does not measure the accuracy or reliability of results. \u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The p-value represents the probability of obtaining results as extreme or more extreme than observed, assuming the null hypothesis is true.","Statistical significance is conventionally set at p \u003C 0.05, meaning there is less than 5% probability the results occurred by chance.","A p-value does not indicate the size or clinical importance of an observed effect."],"references":["Sullivan LM. Essentials of biostatistics in public health. 3rd ed. Burlington (MA): Jones \u0026 Bartlett Learning; 2018.","Dawson B, Trapp RG. Basic \u0026 clinical biostatistics. 4th ed. New York: McGraw-Hill; 2004."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57152"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17619"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57152","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/57152"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-20T10:36:02+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-20T10:37:57+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10333"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71656"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}